<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-808-996  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 808 996.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  August 20 1990 n382 p87(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>VAR fingers vertical: automated identification-analysis system.andO;(value-added resellers) (North American Morpho Systems Inc.) (lawenforcement) (VAR News)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Grace, Tim.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>North American Morpho Systems Inc sells biometric fingerprintidentification (ID) systems mainly to large law enforcementagencies.andP;  Its latest installation is of a statewide fingerprintclearinghouse system for Missouri.andP;  Morpho's fingerprint analysispackage is based on IBM RT workstations and the company's ownsoftware and includes installation, training and support.andP;  Itprovides an user-friendly, highly accurate means of analysis viasophisticated displays, cameras, image processing, storage andretrieval technology.andP;  Customers include such states as NewJersey, New York and Hawaii, France's Ministry of NationalAffairs, the Royal Hong Kong Police Force and police departmentsin Oklahoma City and Los Angeles.andP;  These agencies believe anautomated ID system justifies its high initial cost by increasingthe odds of solving a crime by 10 percent and reducing the cost ofsolution per crime by perhaps 90 percent.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   North American Morpho Systems Inc. (products).andO;Topic:     Vertical MarketLaw EnforcementSpecial-Purpose ComputersValue-Added ResellersBiometrics.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>